Very emotional and raw caption ahead…

Hope. This is what Easter means to me. For the last few years, I’ve been aggressively deconstructing religious trauma from the ICOC cult I grew up in that forever distorted my view on life, spirituality, and higher power. 

But one thing I know for certain, regardless of the anger I feel toward my own religious background, is that God is alive.

I’ve almost lost hope so many times, especially lately. My depression has been excruciatingly painful. My chronic pain has taken so many sunny days away from me.

But seeing God bring us through miscarriage, pulling me out of almost taking my own life many times, creating an unconditional and unbreakable love between myself and my husband, and blessing us with our beautiful baby girl after doctors telling us she wouldn’t be a viable pregnancy… all of these things give me hope. 

Hope for a resolution to my inner turmoil.
Hope for a bright and safe future for my daughter.
Hope for happiness through my depression and intrusive thoughts.
Hope for healing.
Hope for figuring out the true dynamic between God and myself.

Hope that the parts of us that feel broken will be made whole.

The depths of our pain magnify the heights of our joy. As I reflect on that pain, I feel an overwhelming gratitude for joy against all odds.

Whatever you believe… believe in hope.
Happy Easter.
